&nbsp;</p>
<!--break-->
<p>There is a newly renovated auditorium that has the capacity for 60 people. The branch is set up for wireless use by the public. There are 10 laptops available for public use.&nbsp; **There is a circulation desk near the entrance where patrons can return items, checkout items and register for library cards. There are two information desks, one in the adult/ young adult section and one in the children&rsquo;s section.<br />
The public area consists of an Adult/ Young Adult section and a Children section. The Adult/ Young Adult collection consists of&nbsp; Fiction, Non-fiction, New Books, Paperbacks, Graphic Novels, DVDs, CDs, Books on CD and Cassette Tape, Videos, Magazines, Newspapers, Large Print, Reference and World Languages. The World Languages section has books and DVDs in Italian, Spanish, French, Chinese, Russian and Albanian. There are 10 full service desktop computers and 2 catalog computers available for the public. <br />
The children&rsquo;s section consists of Picture Books, Easy Books, Young Readers, Fairy Tales, Fiction, Non-fiction, DVDs, CDs, Books on CD and Cassette Tape, Videos, Parenting Collection, Holiday, Reference and Reading Room. There are 7 full service desktop computers and 1 catalog computer.</p>
<p>There is a combination circulation/ information desk near the entrance where patrons can return items, checkout items, register for library cards and ask information questions.<br />
<br />
<br />
THE BRANCH WILL BE COMBINING THE CIRCULATION AND INFORMATION DESK IN A FEW WEEKS.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2009-02-17 12:05:46 -0500', '2013-03-04 15:34:09 -0500', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO locations ("loc_id", "name", "description", "phone", "fax", "tty", "email", "handicapped_access", "activities", "created", "modified", "amenities", "socialmedia", "floorplan", "division_referral") VALUES (457, '<main>', '<p>The New York Public Library''s Mulberry Street Branch Library is located at the site of a former chocolate factory in the SoHo neighborhood of Manhattan, historically known as the Cast Iron District.</p>
<!--break-->
<p>The Branch entrance is located at ground level, and two other floors are located below ground. A prominent staircase connects the spaces and brings natural light downstairs. Designed with respect to the building''s infrastructure, history, and context, new materials of wood and metal provide a dynamic contrast to the existing fabric of brick, cast iron, and heavy timber beams.</p>', '2129663424', NULL, NULL, 'Mulberry_Branch@nypl.org', NULL, NULL, '2009-02-17 13:08:53 -0500', '2013-09-18 17:33:20 -0400', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
